Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef and Pork Mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt and @pepper. 
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the mince fries, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Once the mince is cooked, add the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, @Tomato Passata{1%carton} and @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g} along with the @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, preheat your #grill{} to high.

Halve the @Ciabatta{2}.

Put your ciabatta halves cut-side up on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Grill until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the ragu has thickened, taste and add @salt, @pepper and @?Sugar{} if needed.

Once the ciabatta has toasted, remove from the grill and carefully spoon the ragu on top of each half.

Sprinkle over the cheese and grill again until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Dressing ==

While the ciabattas are under the grill, in a #large bowl{}, combine the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml}, @Sugar for the Dressing{1%tsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt and @pepper and mix together.

Add the carrot and @Baby Leaf Mix{50%g} to the dressing and toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Share the loaded ciabattas between your plates.

Serve your salad alongside. Enjoy!